text: five things you're doing that make
people dislike you immediately sharing
too many photos on social media posting
too many photos might alienate people
according to one study that looked at
508 Facebook users posting too many
family photos may alienate friends and
posting too many photos of friends may
alienate family so keep some photos to
yourself name-dropping one study had
people name dropped tennis pro Roger
Federer in emails the more they stressed
their association with Federer the less
light they were by their colleague
participants said the email sounded
manipulative humble bragging most people
do this in job interviews saying things
like I work too hard or I care too much
a Harvard study shows that will hurt
your odds of getting hired instead state
a real weakness that isn't a deal
breaker
hiding your emotions researchers showed
students two different videos of an
actor's face the actor would either show
emotion or remain emotionless while they
watched funny or sad scenes from a movie
students rated the emotive actor much
higher in likability not smiling a study
took 100 students and showed them photos
of people posing researchers found no
matter how the person in the photo posed
people liked the most if they were
smiling a different study found that
smiling made you more memorable after
meeting someone for the first time of
course simply not being a jerk couldn't
hurt either
